pig-sticking
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number:
Definition:hunting with dogs of wild pigs which when bailed up are killed by stabbing rather than by shooting.; hunting wild pigs with a sheath knife (and dogs)
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain:[none]
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: in DNZE; cf. ODE; usually hyphenated but aka pig sticking, pigsticking
